docs: Multi-signature smart contract implementation.
Acts like a wallet that needs multiple signers for any action performed.
See the readme file for more detailed documentation.
abi.name: Multisig

docs: Allows the contract to receive funds even if it is marked as unpayable in the protocol.
endpoints.name: deposit

docs: Returns `true` (`1`) if the user has signed the action.
Does not check whether or not the user is still a board member and the signature valid.
endpoints.name: signed

docs: Used by board members to sign actions.
endpoints.name: sign

docs: Board members can withdraw their signatures if they no longer desire for the action to be executed.
Actions that are left with no valid signatures can be then deleted to free up storage.
endpoints.name: unsign

docs: Clears storage pertaining to an action that is no longer supposed to be executed.
Any signatures that the action received must first be removed, via `unsign`.
Otherwise this endpoint would be prone to abuse.
endpoints.name: discardAction

docs: Minimum number of signatures needed to perform any action.
endpoints.name: getQuorum

docs: Denormalized board member count.
It is kept in sync with the user list by the contract.
endpoints.name: getNumBoardMembers

docs: Denormalized proposer count.
It is kept in sync with the user list by the contract.
endpoints.name: getNumProposers

docs: The index of the last proposed action.
0 means that no action was ever proposed yet.
endpoints.name: getActionLastIndex

docs: Initiates board member addition process.
Can also be used to promote a proposer to board member.
endpoints.name: proposeAddBoardMember

docs: Initiates proposer addition process..
Can also be used to demote a board member to proposer.
endpoints.name: proposeAddProposer

docs: Removes user regardless of whether it is a board member or proposer.
endpoints.name: proposeRemoveUser

docs: Propose a transaction in which the contract will perform a transfer-execute call.
Can send EGLD without calling anything.
Can call smart contract endpoints directly.
Doesn't really work with builtin functions.
endpoints.name: proposeTransferExecute

docs: Propose a transaction in which the contract will perform a transfer-execute call.
Can call smart contract endpoints directly.
Can use ESDTTransfer/ESDTNFTTransfer/MultiESDTTransfer to send tokens, while also optionally calling endpoints.
Works well with builtin functions.
Cannot simply send EGLD directly without calling anything.
endpoints.name: proposeAsyncCall

docs: Returns `true` (`1`) if `getActionValidSignerCount >= getQuorum`.
endpoints.name: quorumReached

docs: Proposers and board members use this to launch signed actions.
endpoints.name: performAction

docs: Not used internally, just to retrieve results via endpoint.
